---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="SEO for SaaS Companies — Meridian" description="Meridian builds organic content engines for SaaS companies. Programmatic SEO, comparison pages, integration content, and full-funnel tracking from content to trial signup.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-dark to-dark-card pt-32 pb-20 md:pb-28">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6">
      <p class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent mb-6">SEO for SaaS</p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-extrabold text-hero-text leading-[1.05] tracking-tight max-w-4xl">
        Organic growth.<br />Built for product<br />companies.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-body-muted max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        SaaS SEO is not blog posts. It's comparison pages that steal competitor traffic, integration pages that capture bottom-of-funnel intent, and a content engine that compounds — so you're not dependent on paid acquisition forever.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/audit" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-accent hover:bg-accent-hover text-white text-sm font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Get a free SEO audit &rarr;
        </a>
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 border border-dark-border text-body-muted hover:text-white hover:border-white/20 text-sm font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Talk to us
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Problem -->
  <section class="bg-white py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-dark leading-tight mb-6">The paid acquisition trap.</h2>
      <p class="text-light-text text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Most SaaS companies pour budget into paid ads and get a predictable but expensive growth curve. The moment the budget pauses, so does growth. CAC climbs as the channel gets competitive. And organic sits untouched — full of compounding potential that never gets built.
      </p>
      <p class="text-light-text text-lg leading-relaxed">
        We build the organic side of the equation. Content that ranks before a prospect talks to sales. Pages that show up when someone Googles your competitor. Guides that answer the exact question your ICP is asking at 11pm. Not instead of paid — alongside it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What We Actually Build -->
  <section class="bg-hero-text py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6">
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-dark leading-tight">What we actually build for SaaS.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-light-text text-lg max-w-2xl">Four content types that consistently drive qualified organic traffic for product companies.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">

        <!-- Comparison Pages -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-accent/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <span class="text-accent text-xl font-bold">⇄</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3">Comparison & Alternative Pages</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
            "Best alternative to [Competitor]" and "[Your Product] vs [Competitor]" pages capture high-intent searches from prospects already in buying mode. These are the highest-converting pages on any SaaS site.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-accent font-medium">→ Targets: problem-aware, competitor-aware searches</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature Pages -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-accent/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <span class="text-accent text-xl font-bold">⊞</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3">Programmatic Feature Pages</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
            One landing page per feature, built for the specific query that feature solves. "[Feature] for [use case]", "[Feature] software", "[problem] tool". Scales without writing each one from scratch.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-accent font-medium">→ Targets: solution-aware, feature-specific searches</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Integration Pages -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-accent/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <span class="text-accent text-xl font-bold">⟳</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3">Integration & "How To" Pages</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
            "[Your tool] + [Other tool]" integration pages and "how to do X with [Your product]" guides capture bottom-of-funnel intent — searchers who are already using adjacent tools and evaluating yours.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-accent font-medium">→ Targets: bottom-of-funnel, evaluation-stage searches</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Problem-Aware Content -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 border border-gray-200">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-accent/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center mb-5">
            <span class="text-accent text-xl font-bold">↯</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-dark mb-3">Problem-Aware Content</h3>
          <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed mb-4">
            Blog and landing content targeting searches your ICP runs before they know your product exists. Ranks for the problem, introduces your solution, and builds authority with buyers at the top of the funnel.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-accent font-medium">→ Targets: problem-aware, not-yet-solution-aware searches</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tracking -->
  <section class="bg-white py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-dark leading-tight mb-6">We track content → trial. Not just traffic.</h2>
      <p class="text-light-text text-lg leading-relaxed mb-10">
        Most SEO agencies report on rankings and sessions. That's not useful if you're a SaaS company — you need to know which content is actually driving trial signups and activations.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 bg-hero-text rounded-xl border border-gray-200">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mt-0.5">01</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-dark">Impression → Click → Session</p>
            <p class="text-light-text text-sm mt-1">Standard GSC + GA4 funnel — what's getting found, what's getting clicked, what's landing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 bg-hero-text rounded-xl border border-gray-200">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mt-0.5">02</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-dark">Session → Trial Signup</p>
            <p class="text-light-text text-sm mt-1">Which organic landing pages are converting visitors into signups. Not just aggregate traffic — per-page conversion tracking.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 bg-hero-text rounded-xl border border-gray-200">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mt-0.5">03</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-dark">Trial → Activation</p>
            <p class="text-light-text text-sm mt-1">Where we can connect GA4 events to product activation milestones — we do. Content that drives activated users is different from content that drives bounced signups.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 bg-hero-text rounded-xl border border-gray-200">
          <span class="text-accent font-bold text-lg mt-0.5">04</span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-dark">CAC Attribution</p>
            <p class="text-light-text text-sm mt-1">Monthly organic CAC estimate vs. your paid CAC — so you have a real number for what the content engine is worth.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works -->
  <section class="bg-hero-text py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-dark leading-tight mb-12">How it works.</h2>
      <div class="space-y-12">
        <div class="flex gap-6">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-dark mb-2">ICP & Keyword Mapping</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">We map your ideal customer profile to search intent — what they search before they know you exist, when they're evaluating, and when they're comparing you to competitors. This becomes the foundation for everything.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-dark mb-2">Technical Audit & Fix</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">Daily automated crawl of your site. Broken pages, missing metadata, slow load times, indexability issues — surfaced and prioritized before they cost you rankings.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-dark mb-2">Content Production</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">Comparison pages, feature pages, integration pages, and problem-aware content — built on a consistent weekly cadence. Drafts delivered in your CMS format, ready to publish.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-6">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">4</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-dark mb-2">Full-Funnel Tracking</h3>
            <p class="text-light-text leading-relaxed">Every piece of content is tracked through your funnel. You see which pages drive signups, not just sessions. Monthly reporting connects organic content to real business outcomes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-dark to-dark-card py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-[44px] font-semibold text-hero-text leading-tight">Ready to build the organic channel?</h2>
      <p class="mt-6 text-body-muted text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto">We'll audit your current SEO, map the highest-leverage content opportunities, and show you exactly what we'd build first.</p>
      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/audit" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 bg-accent hover:bg-accent-hover text-white font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Get a free SEO audit &rarr;
        </a>
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-4 border border-dark-border text-body-muted hover:text-white hover:border-white/20 font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors">
          Talk to us first
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
